<subSubSection id="D984653DFFE7FF9AF4CBFEE540D7C8B1" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="912136B6FFE7FF9AF4CBFEE545EFCBD9" blockId="5.[151,1437,293,678]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF4CBFEE5457BCB29" bold="true" box="[151,287,293,318]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Comments.</emphasis>
As per the molecular revision by 
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFE7FF9AF6B7FEE54067CB29" author="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W." box="[747,1027,293,318]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="769 - 788" refId="ref72510" refString="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W. (2011) Molecular Phylogeny of the Valvatacea (Asteroidea, Echinodermata). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 161, 769 - 788. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2010.00659. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Mah and Foltz (2011)</bibRefCitation>
, the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF013FEE5414DCB29" box="[1103,1321,293,318]" class="Asteroidea" family="Pseudarchasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Pseudarchasteridae</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF4CBFE894522CB75" box="[151,326,329,354]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Pseudarchaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF4CBFE894522CB75" box="[151,326,329,354]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Pseudarchaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF5D2FE8A4643CB76" box="[398,551,330,353]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Paragonaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF5D2FE8A4643CB76" box="[398,551,330,353]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Paragonaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, were removed to the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF713FE8947A8CB75" authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1884" box="[847,972,329,354]" class="Asteroidea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Paxillosida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="order">Paxillosida</taxonomicName>
and are not included herein. Several goniasterid-like genera, including 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF671FEAE46E4CB92" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[557,640,366,389]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Fromia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF671FEAE46E4CB92" box="[557,640,366,389]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Fromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF698FEAD4725CB91" authorityName="Livingstone" authorityYear="1931" box="[708,833,365,390]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Neoferdina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF698FEAD4725CB91" box="[708,833,365,390]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Neoferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which have historically been included within the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF4CBFE51452CCBBD" box="[151,328,401,426]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Ophidiasteridae</taxonomicName>
were also re-classified within the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF693FE514008CBBE" authority="(Mah and Foltz 2011)" authorityName="Mah and Foltz" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Mah and Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[719,1132,401,426]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">
Goniasteridae (
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFE7FF9AF726FE514000CBBE" author="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W." box="[890,1124,401,426]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="769 - 788" refId="ref72510" refString="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W. (2011) Molecular Phylogeny of the Valvatacea (Asteroidea, Echinodermata). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 161, 769 - 788. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.2010.00659. x" type="journal article" year="2011">Mah and Foltz 2011</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This is dealt with in more detail by 
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFE7FF9AF4A3FE7545E3CBD9" author="Mah, C. L." box="[255,391,437,462]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 72" refId="ref72305" refString="Mah, C. L. (2017) Overview of the Ferdina - like Goniasteridae (Echinodermata: Asteroidea) including a new subfamily, three new genera and fourteen new species. Zootaxa, 4271 (1), 1 - 72. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4271.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Mah (2017)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="912136B6FFE7FF9AF49BFE1940D7C8B1" blockId="5.[151,1437,293,678]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Several members of the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF589FE194606CBE5" box="[469,610,473,498]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Oreasteridae</taxonomicName>
have historically been treated as members of the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF0D5FE19414CCBE5" baseAuthorityName="Mah and Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1161,1320,473,498]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
, including 
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF4CBFE3D4585C801" box="[151,481,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF4CBFE3D4526C801" authorityName="H. L. Clark" authorityYear="1909" box="[151,322,509,534]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Goniodiscaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Goniodiscaster</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF511FE3D4585C801" authorityName="Doderlein" authorityYear="1916" box="[333,481,509,534]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Monachaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Monachaster</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF644FE3D46A6C801" box="[536,706,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF644FE3D46DFC801" authorityName="Dollfus" authorityYear="1936" box="[536,699,509,534]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Stellasteropsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Stellasteropsis</taxonomicName>
;
</emphasis>
these genera and 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF7D1FE3D4793C801" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1840" box="[909,1015,509,534]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" genus="Anthenea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF7D1FE3D4793C801" box="[909,1015,509,534]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Anthenea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are all assigned to the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF0A5FE3D41FCC801" baseAuthorityName="Mah and Foltz" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1273,1432,509,534]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
. The traditional oreasterid assignment appears to have been based largely on robust skeletal development, argued here to be unreliable as a synapomorphy. 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF630FD8646A4C84A" box="[620,704,582,605]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Nectria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF630FD8646A4C84A" box="[620,704,582,605]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Nectria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for example, shares numerous characters shared with 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF176FD8541F8C849" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1857" box="[1322,1436,581,606]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Mediaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF176FD8541F8C849" box="[1322,1436,581,606]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Mediaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other members of the “ 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF5B2FDA9463BC895" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1857" box="[494,607,617,642]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Mediaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF5B2FDA9463BC895" box="[494,607,617,642]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Mediaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” clade, including 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF718FDAA47C2C896" authorityName="Perrier" authorityYear="1894" box="[836,934,618,641]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Rosaster" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3EAEAA4FFE7FF9AF718FDAA47C2C896" box="[836,934,618,641]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Rosaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has been incorrectly assigned in the 
<taxonomicName id="569E4D35FFE7FF9AF4CBFD4D4540C8B1" box="[151,292,653,678]" class="Asteroidea" family="Oreasteridae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Oreasteridae</taxonomicName>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation id="F50F4B47FFE7FF9AF537FD4E4602C8B1" author="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J." box="[363,614,653,678]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" pagination="1 - 510" refId="ref73976" refString="Rowe, F. W. E. &amp; Gates, J. (1995) Echinodermata. In: Wells, A. (Ed.), Zoological Catalogue of Australia. Fol. 33. CSIRO, Melbourne, pp. 1 - 510. https: // doi. org / 10.1086 / 419606" type="book chapter" year="1995">Gates and Rowe 1995</bibRefCitation>
). These genera are discussed in further detail herein.
</paragraph>
